FF;URL Address;;url_part
XF;URL address should start with file location as 'file:///' or 'http://'. When URL address starts with 'http://', a following server location can be specified as IP address or hostname. Hostname should be set as Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN), e.g. SubDomain.DomainName.DocumentServer.iskratel.si. The rest of the URL address represents fileName e.g. DirectoryName/SubDirectoryName/FileName. Practical examples: http://ntmaketaxx.iskratel.si/fileName, http://ntmaketaxx.iskratel.si:8080/fileName

E;m.WZ_MU_File.class;Subscriber;WZ_MU_File;CMG
FF;File;;$transient
XF;The file for the multiple update of subscribers consists of the Area Code and the Directory Number data pairs, separated by a hyphen. Other data are set regarding to the type of subscriber: - Analog & ISDN Subscribers: just Area Code and the Directory Number should be defined   Example: 04-2072730   04-2072623 ... - SIP Suscriber: In the case when the Supplementary Service Set, Call Server Address, Domain Name and/or the Identification Alias should also be updated, these data are also defined.   Example: 04-2072730    supplServiceSet=15 domainName=null identAlias=null   04-2072623    supplServiceSet=14 domainName=null identAlias=null  ... - MGCP Subscriber: also IP Address and Domain Name should be defined.   Example: 04-2072730   172.18.241.142   [172.18.241.142]   04-2072623   172.18.241.136   mg1.iskratel.si ...
FE;File;;$transient
XE;The file for the multiple update of subscribers consists of the Area Code and the Directory Number data pairs, separated by a hyphen. Other data are set regarding to the type of subscriber: - Analog & ISDN Subscribers: just Area Code and the Directory Number should be defined   Example: 04-2072730   04-2072623 ... - SIP Suscriber: In the case when the Supplementary Service Set, Call Server Address, Domain Name and/or the Identification Alias should also be updated, these data are also defined.   Example: 04-2072730    supplServiceSet=15 domainName=null identAlias=null   04-2072623    supplServiceSet=14 domainName=null identAlias=null  ... - MGCP Subscriber: also IP Address and Domain Name should be defined.   Example: 04-2072730   172.18.241.142   [172.18.241.142]   04-2072623   172.18.241.136   mg1.iskratel.si ...

DF;c.h323ToneProfileSpecifAll
VF;false;Only Specified
VF;true;All, by Terminal
FF;Only Selected Local Tones Generated;;$virtual
XF;Manual setting allowed
FF;All Local Tones Generated by Terminal;;$virtual
XF;All local tones are supposed to be generated by terminal or terminal adapter
FF;Dial Tone;;$virtual
XF;If checked then dial tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself
DF;c.BooleanYesNo
VF;false;No
VF;true;Yes
FF;Alert Tone;;$virtual
XF;If checked then ring tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself but only when terminating side does not generate ring tone.
FF;Busy Tone;;$virtual
XF;If checked then busy tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides busy tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DF;c.BooleanYesNo
VF;false;No
VF;true;Yes
FF;Congestion Tone;;$virtual
XF;If checked then congestion tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides congestion tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DF;c.BooleanYesNo
VF;false;No
VF;true;Yes
FF;Confirmation Tone;;$virtual
XF;If checked then confirmation tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides confirmation tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DF;c.BooleanYesNo
VF;false;No
VF;true;Yes
FF;Rejection;;$virtual
XF;If checked then rejection tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides rejection tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DF;c.BooleanYesNo
VF;false;No
VF;true;Yes
FF;Preemption Tone;;$virtual
XF;If checked then preemption tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides preemption tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified in case of disconnect. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DF;c.BooleanYesNo
VF;false;No
VF;true;Yes
FF;Hold Tone;;$virtual
XF;If checked then generation of hold tone or music on hold is responsibility of the terminal or terminal adapter itself. If not checked hold tone or music on hold is generated by media server controlled by call server.
DF;c.BooleanYesNo
VF;false;No

DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Alert Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then ring tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself but only when terminating side does not generate ring tone.
CE;Busy Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then busy tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides busy tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Congestion Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then congestion tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides congestion tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Confirmation Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then confirmation tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides confirmation tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Rejection;;$virtual
XE;If checked then rejection tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides rejection tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Preemption Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then preemption tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides preemption tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified in case of disconnect. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.

XE;All local tones are supposed to be generated by terminal or terminal adapter
CE;Dial Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then dial tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Alert Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then ring tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself but only when terminating side does not generate ring tone.
CE;Busy Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then busy tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides busy tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Congestion Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then congestion tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides congestion tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Confirmation Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then confirmation tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides confirmation tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Rejection;;$virtual
XE;If checked then rejection tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides rejection tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Preemption Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then preemption tone is supposed to be generated by terminal itself. Otherwise the call server provides preemption tone from media server. The SIP signal flow is modified in case of disconnect. Call is not released immediately, RTP session is established instead. BYE is sent after timeout expire.
DE;c.BooleanYesNo
VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
CE;Hold Tone;;$virtual
XE;If checked then generation of hold tone or music on hold is responsibility of the terminal or terminal adapter itself. If not checked hold tone or music on hold is generated by media server controlled by call server.

VE;false;No
VE;true;Yes
